Quality check 03, List blocks in block groups split by community districts

Satya Golla and Steve Simon

Created 2023-03-30

This program lists blocks within block groups that only partially intersect with community districts.

Load relevant files

# Important abbreviations:
#    bg = block group
#    bl = block
#    cd = community district
#    co = county
#    nbd=neighborhood
#    tr = tract

library(dplyr)
path_name <- "../data/"
terse <- TRUE
conditional_glimpse <- function(x) {
  if (terse) return(invisible())
  cat("\n\n")
  cat(deparse(substitute(x)))
  cat("\n\n")
  glimpse(x)
  cat("\n\n")
  return(invisible())
}

test1 <- data.frame(x=1:3, y=4:6)
conditional_glimpse(test1)

Test acs download

library(tidycensus)
county_list <- c(
  "Johnson",
  "Leavenworth",
  "Wyandotte",
  "Cass",
  "Clay",
  "Jackson",
  "Platte")
state_list <- rep(c("KS", "MO"), c(3,4))

vlist <- c("B01001_003", "B01001_027")
load_variables(2020, "acs5", cache = TRUE) %>%
  filter(name %in% vlist)
## # A tibble: 2 x 3
##   name       label                                    concept   
##   <chr>      <chr>                                    <chr>     
## 1 B01001_003 Estimate!!Total:!!Male:!!Under 5 years   SEX BY AGE
## 2 B01001_027 Estimate!!Total:!!Female:!!Under 5 years SEX BY AGE
acs_children <- NULL
for (i in 1:7) {
  acs1 <- get_acs(
    geography = "cbg", 
    variables = vlist, 
    state=state_list[i],
    county=county_list[i],
    year = 2020)
  acs_children <- rbind(acs_children, acs1)
}

Subset co to seven counties

clist <- c(
  "20091",
  "20103",
  "20209",
  "29037",
  "29047",
  "29095",
  "29165")
co                                     %>%
  filter(GEOID %in% clist)             -> co
conditional_glimpse(co)

Get id values for all community districts

cd                                     %>%
  tibble                               %>%
  distinct(cd_id)                      %>%
  arrange(cd_id)                       %>%
  pull(cd_id)                           -> cd_list

library(tidycensus)
county_list <- c(
  "Johnson",
  "Leavenworth",
  "Wyandotte",
  "Cass",
  "Clay",
  "Jackson",
  "Platte")

vlist <- c("B01001_003", "B01001_027")
load_variables(2020, "acs5", cache = TRUE) %>%
  filter(name %in% vlist)

    geography = "cbg", 
    variables = vlist, 
    state=state_list[i],

    year = 2020)
  acs_children <- rbind(acs_children, acs1)
}
